---
export const prerender = true;
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import WordCounter from '../../components/tools/WordCounter';
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How accurate is this word counter?",
    answer: "Our word counter is 100% accurate for standard text. It counts words by splitting on whitespace, counts all characters including spaces separately, and calculates sentences by detecting punctuation endings. Numbers like '2026' count as one word."
  },
  {
    question: "What is the ideal word count for a blog post?",
    answer: "For SEO in 2026, blog posts should target 1,500 to 2,500 words for competitive topics. Pillar articles and guides should reach 3,000 to 5,000 words. Landing pages work best at 500 to 1,200 words. Google considers content under 300 words as thin content."
  },
  {
    question: "How many characters are allowed in a Twitter post?",
    answer: "Twitter/X allows 280 characters per post. Our character counter tracks this in real time so you never exceed the limit. For LinkedIn, posts perform best at 150 to 300 words. Instagram captions cap at 2,200 characters."
  },
  {
    question: "How is reading time calculated?",
    answer: "Reading time is based on the average adult reading speed of 238 words per minute. Speak time uses 130 words per minute — the average conversational pace. A 1,000-word article takes approximately 4 minutes to read and 8 minutes to present aloud."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this tool work without internet?",
    answer: "Once the page loads, the word counter works entirely in your browser using JavaScript. All counting happens locally on your device — no data is sent to servers, making it fully private and functional offline after the initial page load."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I use this for SEO meta description writing?",
    answer: "Yes. Google displays meta descriptions up to 155 characters and title tags up to 60 characters before truncating them in search results. Use our character counter to stay within these limits. Pair it with our free Meta Description Generator for best results."
  },
];
---
<ToolLayout title="Free Word & Character Counter - No Signup Required" description="Count words, characters, sentences, paragraphs with reading time and keyword density." keywords="word counter, character counter, online word count, count words free, word count checker, reading time calculator, character count tool" toolCategory="Text Utility" faqs={faqs}>
  <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 sm:p-8">
    <WordCounter client:visible />
  </div>
<div class="mt-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Free Word Counter — Count Words & Characters Online</h2>
    <p>Our free word counter tool instantly counts words, characters, sentences, paragraphs, and reading time as you type. Whether you are writing a blog post, academic essay, social media caption, or SEO meta description, knowing your exact word and character count helps you stay within limits and hit your targets.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">Why Word Count Matters for Writers and SEO</h3>
    <p>Word count directly affects SEO performance. Google favors long-form content between 1,500 and 2,500 words for competitive topics. Blog posts under 300 words are considered thin content and may be penalized. For social media, Twitter/X allows 280 characters, LinkedIn posts perform best at 150-300 words, and Instagram captions cap at 2,200 characters. Our word counter tracks all of these metrics simultaneously so you never have to count manually again.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">Character Count for Meta Descriptions and SEO</h3>
    <p>When writing meta descriptions for your pages, staying within 150-160 characters is critical. Characters beyond this limit get cut off in Google search results, reducing your click-through rate. Use our word counter alongside our <a href="/tools/meta-description-generator" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">free Meta Description Generator</a> to craft perfectly sized descriptions every time. Similarly, title tags should stay under 60 characters to display correctly in search results.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">Reading Time and Speak Time Estimates</h3>
    <p>Our tool calculates reading time based on the average adult reading speed of 238 words per minute, and speak time based on 130 words per minute — the average speaking pace. These estimates help podcasters, video script writers, and presenters plan their content length accurately. A 1,000-word article takes approximately 4 minutes to read and 8 minutes to present.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8">How to Use This Tool for Academic Writing</h3>
    <p>Students and academics frequently face strict word count requirements. Essays, dissertations, and research papers often have minimum and maximum word counts enforced by institutions. Paste your text into our counter and get an instant breakdown. If you need to expand your content, our <a href="/tools/ai-paraphraser" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">AI Paraphraser</a> can help rewrite sections in different styles to meet your target length.</p>
  </article>

  <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Free Tools</h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <a href="/tools/meta-description-generator" class="tool-card group">
        <span class="text-2xl">🏷️</span>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-blue-600 mt-2">Meta Description Generator</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Generate SEO-optimized meta descriptions</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/tools/ai-paraphraser" class="tool-card group">
        <span class="text-2xl">🔄</span>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-blue-600 mt-2">AI Paraphraser</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Rewrite text in different styles</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/tools/case-converter" class="tool-card group">
        <span class="text-2xl">🔤</span>
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-blue-600 mt-2">Case Converter</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Convert text to any case format</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</ToolLayout>
